Subject: [PATCH v19, 15/19] media: mtk-vcodec: Support 34bits dma address for vdec
Date:   Thu, 13 Jan 2022 12:10:51 +0800
Message-ID: <20220113041055.25213-16-yunfei.dong@mediatek.com>
X-Mailer: git-send-email 2.25.1
In-Reply-To: <20220113041055.25213-1-yunfei.dong@mediatek.com>
References: <20220113041055.25213-1-yunfei.dong@mediatek.com>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7BIT
Content-Type:   text/plain; charset=US-ASCII
X-MTK:  N
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-media.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-media@vger.kernel.org

Use the dma_set_mask_and_coherent helper to set vdec
DMA bit mask to support 34bits iova space(16GB) that
the mt8192 iommu HW support.

Whole the iova range separate to 0~4G/4G~8G/8G~12G/12G~16G,
regarding which iova range VDEC actually locate, it
depends on the dma-ranges property of vdec dtsi node.

Signed-off-by: Yunfei Dong <yunfei.dong@mediatek.com>
Reviewed-by: AngeloGioacchino Del Regno <angelogioacchino.delregno@collabora.com>
---
